        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Doctor: expose systemd linger findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add default-disabled structured lint findings for `core/doctor/systemd-linger`\n- keep legacy interactive/non-interactive linger enablement in the existing Doctor run paths\n- report only the actionable `linger=no` state for local Linux mode; unavailable systemd/loginctl and already-enabled lingering stay quiet\n\n## Validation\n\n- `CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm exec oxfmt --write src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (51 tests)\n- `CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/plugin-sdk-surface-report.mjs --check`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n\n## Proof\n\nFocused source test proof covers the behavior directly:\n\n- default lint skips `core/doctor/systemd-linger` because it is `defaultEnabled: false`\n- explicit `--only core/doctor/systemd-linger` runs the check\n- mocked disabled linger emits warning metadata with `target: systemd.user.alice` and `fixHint: Run: sudo loginctl enable-linger alice`\n\nI did not use the local WSL source CLI transcript as proof because the WSL wrapper polluted/mangled the captured JSON during probing. The source tests and `check:changed` proof are clean.\n\n## Contract\n\nNo config schema, plugin manifest, SDK, persisted data model, or repair-path contract change. This adds only an opt-in structured Doctor lint finding for existing systemd-linger health behavior.",
